FBIS4-32076 "dreeu118_m_94003" FBIS-EEU-94-118 Daily Report 17 Jun 1994 THE FORMER YUGOSLAV REPUBLIC OF MACEDONIA Minister Counsels Calm Over Border Incidents Minister Counsels Calm Over Border Incidents AU1706151794 Skopje MILS-NEWS in English 17 Jun 94 AU1706151794 Skopje MILS-NEWS English BFN [Unattributed report: "No Need To Heat Up Tension"] [Text] Macedonian [The Former Yugoslav Republic of Macedonia -- FYROM] Defense Minister is presently on a visit to Paris, participating in the debate on security in Europe. In his telephone interview for Radio Skopje, concerning the current situation on the Macedonian-Serbian border, he stated all the facts he had pointed out 10 days ago, at his lecture for the Macedonian Army field officers, are current now as they had been then. [sentence as received] Nothing significant has happened in the meantime, he said, adding there is no need to heat up the tension.
